
=== Build Gear [BETA release] ===


1. Introduction

   Build Gear is a lightweight embedded build tool for experienced GNU/Linux
   users and developers. The primary focus of this build tool is to keep it
   simple, which is reflected in a straightforward command line build interface,
   and easy to maintain build files. The secondary focus is build performance
   and build integrity. Build Gear is easy to use and well suited for rapid
   product and prototype development of firmware to deploy in small to medium 
   sized systems.


2. Installation

   See INSTALL file for details on how to build and install Build Gear.


3. Documentation

   Visit http://www.buildgear.org for detailed documentation on how to
   use the Build Gear tool and also on how to create build files.

